This paper presents the experimental demonstration of direct, time-domain temporal coherence measurement of XFEL in LCLS hard x-ray mode. The authors perform the measurement by shifting the x-ray pulse (produced before the phase shifter) and the microbunched electron beam (preserved after the phase shifter) within the scale of coherence length and evaluating the correlation between them. The shift is done by fine tuning the chicane strength between two undulator sections. This paper is well written, the results are understandable, and presented in a clear way. I have a few formatting comments below:

1) In Eq. (1), \lambda_r is not defined;
2) 14-th line from top, right column of p.2, remove famous;
3) Two lines below Eq. (4), supposition should be superposition, and in the following line plane wave should be plane waves;
4) The title of the section Experiment and Conclusion should be formatted in a consistent way to INTRODUCTION and METHOD;
5) Four lines from the bottom, right column of p.4, r ather should be rather;
6) This phase shifter scheme is used to evaluate the temporal coherence in the exponential growth regime; I was wondering if it can be extended to saturation or post-saturation regime. Of course, it requires further extension of the theoretical model, as Bonifacios collective description will fail, thus a priori knowledge might be needed when extracting the experimental measurements.

